          <actionDate>2017-01-03</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Worksite Reporting Act</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Labor to revise regulations under the Occupational Safety and Health Act of 1970 by requiring site-controlling employers to keep a site log for all recordable injuries and illnesses occurring among all employees on the particular site, irrespective of whether such employees are employed directly by the site-controlling employer or are employed by contractors or temporary help or employee leasing services.</p>]]></text>
